findings.details:
ListRequirementsRequest and ListExperiencesRequest use offset-based pagination:
message ListRequirementsRequest {
  int32 page = 1;
  int32 page_size = 2;
  ...
}

Issues:
1. No max page_size limit (could request 1 million items)
2. No default page_size (what if client omits it?)
3. Offset pagination performs poorly on large tables
4. No next_page_token for cursor-based pagination
5. No total_pages or has_more indicator in response

findings.recommendation:
Improve pagination:
message ListRequirementsRequest {
  int32 page_size = 1 [(validate.rules).int32 = {gte: 1, lte: 100}]; // Max 100
  string page_token = 2; // Cursor for next page (empty for first page)
  optional string status = 3;
  optional string priority = 4;
  repeated string tags = 5;
}

message ListRequirementsResponse {
  repeated Requirement requirements = 1;
  string next_page_token = 2; // Empty if no more pages
  int64 total_count = 3; // Total items (expensive to calculate, make optional)
}
